         <!-- end column 1-->
         <!-- start column 2-->
         <div class="col-2-eq-height">
          <h3 style="text-align: center;">
           About Us
          </h3>
          <p>
           Student Leadership &amp; Involvement provides many leadership opportunities at the University
                                 of Utah. Our student leadership programs include ASUU (student government), ULEAD
                                 Leadership programs, Leadership Studies Minor, NSLS and student organizations.
          </p>
         </div>
         <!-- end column 2-->
        </div>
        <div class="row equal-height ">
         <!-- start column 1-->
         <div class="col-3-eq-height">
          <div class="panel">
           <div class="panel-body panel-bg-light">
            <img alt="International Student Night" height="370" src="/_images/homepage/International%20Student%20Night_1200px.jpg" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="555"/>
            <h2 style="text-align: center;">
             <a href="/studentorgs/index.php">
              Student Orgs
             </a>
            </h2>
            <p>
             Getting involved is easy! Want to be a part of student government? Join
             <a href="http://asuu.utah.edu">
              ASUU
             </a>
             . Have a passion or hobby? Join one of more than 600 Recognized Student Organizations
                                       by logging onto
             <a href="http://orgsync.com/login/university-of-utah">
              OrgSync
             </a>
             ! Or
             <a href="/studentorgs/startanorg.php">
              start your own student organization
             </a>
             ! Check out PlazaFest, the largest tabling event for student orgs at the U, during
                                       both the Fall and Spring semesters!
             <a href="http://orgsync.com/login/university-of-utah">
              OrgSync
             </a>
             brings on-campus events and student organizations all onto one exciting platform.
                                       There are tons of
             <a href="/studentorgs/index.php">
              enriching and thriving events
             </a>
             facilitated by our student organizations. If you need help finding the right fit, send
                                       us an email at
             <a href="mailto:studentorgs@utah.edu">
              studentorgs@utah.edu
             </a>
            </p>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
         <!-- end column 1-->
         <!-- start column 2-->
         <div class="col-3-eq-height">
          <div class="panel">
           <div class="panel-body panel-bg-light">
            <p>
             <a href="/SLI%20Statement.png">
              <img alt="Statement" height="800" src="/_images/homepage/SLI%20Statement.png" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="800"/>
             </a>
            </p>
            <p>
             As we conclude our week-long celebration of the life and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther
                                       King, Jr., we are reminded of the importance of a collective voice against racism,
                                       bigotry, and hate. In the past couple of days, stickers from a national hate group
                                       were found on our campus – reported, removed and openly discussed with student groups.
                                       While our campus is an open forum where individuals may express their views, the rhetoric
                                       used by this group does not align with or reflect the University of Utah’s values.
                                       We want to use this incident to encourage our community to engage in respectful dialogue
                                       that enables us to work together and learn, grow, innovate, challenge and build a
                                       better future. Note that stickers can be removed immediately when they are discovered,
                                       and sending information about the location and date (and a photo, if possible) to
                                       the Office of the Dean of Students and/or the Office of Equity and Diversity will
                                       help the campus respond and monitor for others. Please note the message from the University
                                       President regarding this incident:
            </p>
            <p>
             <a href="https://attheu.utah.edu/home-page/condemning-racism-2/">
              https://attheu.utah.edu/home-page/condemning-racism-2/
             </a>
            </p>
            <p>
            </p>
            <p>
            </p>
            <p>
            </p>
            <h2 style="text-align: center;">
            </h2>
